my brother sent of Matthew.

06:05.021 --> 06:06.746
- Mm.
- We should do this someday.

06:06.747 --> 06:07.747
What do you think?

06:07.797 --> 06:08.967
Are you kidding me?
Of course.

06:09.017 --> 06:10.627
I was talking about going
to the water park.

06:10.667 --> 06:12.277
You were talking about
having kids?

06:12.317 --> 06:14.887
Yeah! I said, "Do you think
we can afford it?"

06:14.937 --> 06:17.457
And you said, "We'll start
saving right away."

06:17.497 --> 06:18.677
So let me get this straight.

06:18.717 --> 06:20.547
All that water park money
I've been saving,

06:20.587 --> 06:21.937
you want to spend it
on kids now?

06:21.987 --> 06:23.807
Yeah. Why would you want
to spend that much money

06:23.857 --> 06:24.911
on a water park?

06:24.912 --> 06:26.794
Look, I'm sorry.
I don't know what to say here.

06:26.799 --> 06:28.979
I just...
I never wanted children.

06:29.019 --> 06:30.329
Well, I always have.

06:30.369 --> 06:32.679
All right,
so how do we handle this?

06:32.719 --> 06:34.939
I mean, there's only one
thing to do when two people

06:34.989 --> 06:36.954
have diametrically opposing
views on a subject.

06:36.955 --> 06:38.875
Talk about it lovingly
and decide how to move forward?

06:38.876 --> 06:40.634
- Structured debate.
- Oh. Fun.

06:40.635 --> 06:42.595
High school format.
Modified Lincoln-Douglas.

06:42.645 --> 06:45.425
Let's take one hour apart
for research and prep. Yeah.

06:45.465 --> 06:47.735
Great, I'll just do
a Lincoln-Douglas.

06:47.775 --> 06:50.605
I'd be careful if I were you.
Relationships are like bowels.

06:50.645 --> 06:53.215
Once you get them twisted,
they can never untwist.

06:53.265 --> 06:55.045
Pam, you're in here again.

07:03.445 --> 07:04.160
That's all you prepped?

07:04.162 --> 07:05.202
Yeah, I just searched my heart

07:05.252 --> 07:06.952
and then wrote down
how I was feeling.

07:06.992 --> 07:09.172
I'm gonna eat you alive,
you dumb son of a bitch.

07:09.212 --> 07:11.472
Cool. And then
we'll have kids together?

07:11.522 --> 07:12.782
Yeah. It's gonna be great.

07:12.822 --> 07:14.082
Okay, the topic today

07:14.132 --> 07:16.002
is whether or not
we should have children.

07:16.042 --> 07:17.132
I will be taking
the affirmative.

07:17.172 --> 07:18.302
You will be taking the negative.

07:18.352 --> 07:21.302
Each round will be individually
scored by our judge, Captain Holt.

07:21.303 --> 07:22.733
Do you need to hear
my credentials?

07:22.783 --> 07:25.873
Debate moderator license
D as in delta, 8-1-0...

07:25.913 --> 07:27.833
- I believe you.
- Y as in Yankee, 4-1.

07:27.873 --> 07:30.263
J as in Juliet,
J as in Juliet, 6.

07:30.313 --> 07:31.815
- Great.
- I have a variety of timers.

07:31.817 --> 07:33.427
- Do you prefer a buzz or a ding?
- Don't care.

07:33.467 --> 07:34.295
- Ding.
- Okay.

07:34.296 --> 07:37.036
Peralta, you can present the
first argument from your, uh...

07:37.086 --> 07:39.160
Scribbled list of feelings.

07:39.161 --> 07:40.096
I'll have you know

07:40.097 --> 07:42.290
that I have some
data-driven arguments as well.

07:42.291 --> 07:45.480
According to a study I read,
people with kids

07:45.481 --> 07:47.781
were less likely to report that
they were happy in their lives

07:47.831 --> 07:49.056
than people without kids.

07:49.057 --> 07:52.187
Now, call me crazy, but being
happy tends to make me feel,

07:52.237 --> 07:53.367
uh, pretty happy.

07:53.407 --> 07:54.300
Where did you read this study?

07:54.301 --> 07:57.651
Well, it wasn't something I read
so much as told about.

07:57.701 --> 07:58.831
And who told you about it?

08:01.441 --> 08:03.001
- Hitchcock.
- Hitchcock?

08:03.006 --> 08:03.788
- Yeah.
- That seems like

08:03.789 --> 08:05.930
a pretty intellectual thing
for him to mention.

08:05.934 --> 08:06.864
What was the context?

08:06.865 --> 08:10.135
He had invested in a NuvaRing
competitor called Vag-a-Plug

08:10.136 --> 08:11.777
and was practicing
his sales pitch on me.

08:11.827 --> 08:13.827
This is your first argument?
Your opening statement?

08:13.867 --> 08:14.626
Point to Amy.

08:14.627 --> 08:16.017
All right, fine.
Forget the study.

08:16.057 --> 08:17.797
I just don't want to lose
what we already have.

08:17.847 --> 08:20.017
Ask anyone with children
and they'll tell you

08:20.067 --> 08:23.107
children bring meaning and love
into your life.

08:23.157 --> 08:25.377
Yes, there may be some moments
that you lose,

08:25.417 --> 08:27.377
but there will also be
new moments.

08:27.417 --> 08:28.535
Take the water park.

08:28.536 --> 08:32.535
I would never go with you,
but you know who would?

08:32.586 --> 08:35.068
- Your kid.
- Point to Amy.

08:35.075 --> 08:36.645
That's not your call to make,
Peralta.

08:36.684 --> 08:37.945
Point to Amy.

08:37.985 --> 08:39.905
Okay, fine.
New Subject: work.

08:39.945 --> 08:41.775
We both work way too much.

08:41.815 --> 08:44.385
Why bother having kids if you
never get to spend time with them?

08:44.435 --> 08:46.785
I mean, I love my job,
and I know you love yours,

08:46.825 --> 08:49.062
and I don't think it's fair for either
of us to have to sacrifice that.

08:49.063 --> 08:51.023
Do you know why I want to
become lieutenant so badly?

08:51.025 --> 08:52.685
To prove your worth to
your hyper judgmental parents.

08:52.725 --> 08:53.945
Yes, obviously that.

08:53.985 --> 08:57.075
But also, the higher your rank,
the more control over your hours.

08:57.115 --> 09:00.139
Plenty of people have jobs and
kids, Jake, and they find a way.

09:00.140 --> 09:02.302
This has become more about
your employment status.

09:02.303 --> 09:05.040
As your supervisor, I feel
I have a conflict of interest

09:05.041 --> 09:08.181
- and should abstain from judging.
- Okay, so do we both get a point?

09:08.221 --> 09:09.974
No. Kevin has been
on the phone all this time.

09:09.975 --> 09:11.975
He's also a licensed
debate moderator.

09:12.015 --> 09:14.625
License number
J as in Juliet, 2-5-9...

09:14.675 --> 09:16.415
- This means nothing to me.
- H as in hotel.

09:16.455 --> 09:18.155
- Z as in Zulu.
- Oh, thank God he stopped.

09:18.195 --> 09:19.455
3-6-9.

09:19.505 --> 09:21.335
- Point to Amy.
- Okay, fine.

09:21.375 --> 09:24.945
You want to know why I really
don't want to have children?

09:24.985 --> 09:27.115
I had a crappy dad.

09:27.165 --> 09:28.995
I know what happens
when you mess up as a parent.

09:29.035 --> 09:30.515
It's not great.

09:30.555 --> 09:33.345
And this may come as a shock
to you, but...

09:33.385 --> 09:35.414
I kind of have some dad issues
with certain people.

09:35.415 --> 09:35.975
- Holt.
- Me.

09:35.977 --> 09:37.417
- Raymond.
- Yeah, but not just him.

09:37.457 --> 09:39.937
It's every male authority
figure from my entire life.

09:39.987 --> 09:41.727
Hey, Jake, can you move
"Legends of the Fall"

09:41.767 --> 09:42.817
from new releases into drama?

09:42.857 --> 09:43.897
You got it, Dad.

09:43.947 --> 09:45.907
Craig was only six weeks older
than me.

09:45.947 --> 09:47.257
Since this has become about me,

09:47.297 --> 09:49.127
I'm gonna have to abstain
from this round as well,

09:49.167 --> 09:50.737
but Kevin is still standing by.

09:50.777 --> 09:52.387
Actually, I feel as though
your personal relationship

09:52.427 --> 09:54.087
with Peralta affects me too.

09:54.127 --> 09:55.917
Luckily, I had Gail
standing by as well.

09:55.957 --> 09:57.527
Oh, my God, you guys know Gail?

09:57.567 --> 09:58.334
Who's Gail?

09:58.335 --> 09:59.885
Vice president
of the Debaters Club.

09:59.886 --> 10:01.456
This is a very big deal.

10:01.496 --> 10:02.636
Do you need to hear
my credentials?

10:02.676 --> 10:04.554
License number
U as in uniform, 7...

10:04.555 --> 10:06.735
No!
No more credentials, please.

10:06.775 --> 10:08.125
I don't want to have
a structured debate.

10:08.175 --> 10:09.785
