10:14.808 --> 10:17.978
Amy, I'm scared, okay?

10:18.028 --> 10:20.572
I'm scared that we're gonna have a
child and I won't be able to handle it,

10:20.573 --> 10:22.053
I'm scared that
I'm not gonna be a good father,

10:22.093 --> 10:25.223
and I'm scared that I'll make
a mistake I can't take back.

10:25.273 --> 10:27.923
Jake, I get it.
I'm scared too.

10:27.963 --> 10:29.843
Every other big decision
I've made in my life

10:29.883 --> 10:30.973
I was sure about:

10:31.013 --> 10:32.793
becoming a cop,
asking you to marry me,

10:32.843 --> 10:34.933
buying those Jordan 1s for $500.

10:34.973 --> 10:36.673
Wait, you spent $500
on sneakers?

10:36.713 --> 10:38.503
Yeah, they were so cool,
and if I had never worn them,

10:38.543 --> 10:39.548
they would have kept
their value.

10:39.549 --> 10:41.159
- So they lost their value?
- Yes, all of it.

10:41.199 --> 10:42.769
I stepped in a puddle
as soon as I left the store.

10:42.809 --> 10:43.939
But this isn't about
the Jordans.

10:43.979 --> 10:45.419
This is about the fact

10:45.459 --> 10:47.859
that I don't want to bring
a human being into this world

10:47.899 --> 10:51.689
unless I'm 100% sure that
I'm ready to take care of it.

10:51.729 --> 10:53.469
Okay?

10:53.519 --> 10:55.129
Too emotional.
Point to Amy.

10:55.169 --> 10:56.559
Okay, Gail is clearly biased.

10:56.609 --> 10:58.129
I think we need a new moderator.

10:58.169 --> 10:59.429
Bob Templeman here.

10:59.479 --> 11:01.519
What? How many people
are on this phone call?

11:03.286 --> 11:05.908
Hey, so Holt went to go
smooth things over with Gail.

11:05.909 --> 11:08.259
He thinks we may just have to pay
the Debaters Guild a small fine.

11:08.309 --> 11:10.349
Cool. And as you can see,
Pam is here.

11:10.399 --> 11:11.619
She has some thoughts.

11:11.714 --> 11:13.582
I was saying to Jake,
before Bobby,

11:13.583 --> 11:15.493
I didn't think I wanted
to have kids either.

11:15.495 --> 11:17.801
But he's the best thing
that ever happened to me.

11:17.802 --> 11:19.722
Hey, Pam, could you give us
a minute?

11:19.762 --> 11:22.032
Oh, of course.
I'm gonna call my friend JoAnn.

11:22.072 --> 11:24.902
She's been waiting for
a big update on all of this.

11:24.942 --> 11:25.808
Great.

11:30.122 --> 11:32.602
I'm sorry.
The debate was a bad idea.

11:32.652 --> 11:34.132
I just...

11:34.172 --> 11:36.432
I felt ambushed by the fact
that you didn't want kids,

11:36.482 --> 11:38.092
and I thought I could fix it
with logic.

11:38.132 --> 11:39.612
I mean,
what if I had won the debate?

11:39.652 --> 11:40.962
Jake, I'm trying so hard
to be nice,

11:41.002 --> 11:42.482
but I don't know how to respond
to that.

11:42.522 --> 11:43.662
- Cold-blooded but fair.
- I get it.

11:43.702 --> 11:46.189
You're scared.
I can't change that.

11:46.192 --> 11:48.792
Yeah, but that doesn't mean I'll
never change how I feel about it.

11:48.842 --> 11:51.492
I mean, I used to be scared of
sushi, and now it's my favorite food.

11:51.532 --> 11:53.622
I got tuna sashimi
from a pharmacy the other day.

11:53.672 --> 11:55.282
- You shouldn't have.
- Yeah, it was very warm.

11:55.322 --> 11:56.672
I got so sick.

11:56.712 --> 11:58.852
Look, can we just press pause
on this conversation?

11:58.892 --> 12:00.762
I mean, let's enjoy our lives
for a little bit,

12:00.802 --> 12:02.462
and then maybe the next time
it comes up,

12:02.502 --> 12:04.682
I'll feel differently, okay?

12:07.422 --> 12:08.772
- No.
- What?

12:08.812 --> 12:10.122
I need an answer from you now.

12:10.162 --> 12:11.642
Like right this minute?

12:11.682 --> 12:13.642
You can take a day or a week,

12:13.692 --> 12:14.992
or maybe a month.

12:15.042 --> 12:17.822
That's not a lot of time, Ames.

12:17.862 --> 12:20.042
I mean, that doesn't seem
totally fair.

12:20.082 --> 12:21.482
Well, now you know how I feel.

12:21.522 --> 12:24.092
Women don't have the luxury
of waiting till we're 60

12:24.132 --> 12:26.262
and then changing our minds
and getting remarried

12:26.312 --> 12:28.612
and having a baby
with some dumb 28-year-old.

12:28.662 --> 12:29.702
Oh, come on.

12:29.752 --> 12:31.012
There's no way
I'm gonna be rich enough

12:31.052 --> 12:33.972
that a 28-year-old
is gonna want to be with me.

12:34.012 --> 12:35.232
Did that help?

12:35.272 --> 12:36.802
Look, I don't understand
what the big deal is.

12:36.842 --> 12:38.492
You're still young.
We have plenty of time.

12:38.542 --> 12:40.932
I know, but I don't want
to wait around for two years

12:40.972 --> 12:42.802
and then have you decide
you don't want kids,

12:42.852 --> 12:45.592
'cause I don't want
to start over at 38.

12:45.632 --> 12:48.592
Start over?

12:48.632 --> 12:49.772
Like, with someone else?

12:49.812 --> 12:53.332
<i>♪ Casecation,
all I ever wanted ♪</i>

12:53.382 --> 12:56.252
<i>♪ Casecation, had to get away ♪</i>

12:56.292 --> 12:57.562
<i>♪ Casecation ♪</i>

12:57.602 --> 12:59.692
<i>♪ The vibe in here
is really weird ♪</i>

12:59.732 --> 13:02.002
- I think they're having a fight.
- No, it's not a fight,

13:02.042 --> 13:04.482
it's just a devastatingly sad
conversation

13:04.522 --> 13:06.962
about whether or not we should
have kids or just start over,

13:07.002 --> 13:08.792
so you were totally wrong, Rosa.

13:08.832 --> 13:11.792
What? You got married without
talking about if you want children?

13:11.832 --> 13:13.458
Yeah, and we also got
married without discussing

13:13.459 --> 13:14.182
whether or not we like water parks.

13:14.232 --> 13:15.702
A lot of new stuff has come up,
okay, Terry?

13:15.752 --> 13:17.322
- Why are you guys here?
- A CI came in.

13:17.362 --> 13:18.842
There's a lot of chatter that
whoever tried to kill Rojas

13:18.882 --> 13:19.842
is coming to finish the job.

13:19.882 --> 13:20.932
- At the hospital?
- Yeah.

13:20.972 --> 13:22.452
Holt wanted extra manpower here.

13:22.492 --> 13:24.502
Okay, why don't you two
lock down the nurses' station

13:24.542 --> 13:25.852
while Amy and I secure the room?

13:25.892 --> 13:27.462
Actually,
I'd rather be with Rosa.

13:27.502 --> 13:28.502
- Uh-oh.
- Damn, Jake.

13:28.542 --> 13:30.202
Thanks a lot, Sarge.

13:30.242 --> 13:31.072
You told me to sing!

13:31.112 --> 13:32.552
Yeah, but what was all this?

13:32.592 --> 13:34.382
That's just Terry being Terry.

13:34.422 --> 13:37.292
Okay, from this vantage we can
see the elevator and the stairs.

13:37.342 --> 13:39.552
No one should be able to get
to Rojas without us noticing.

13:39.602 --> 13:41.382
- Cool.
- Hey, look, um...

13:41.432 --> 13:43.382
I don't want you to get caught
in the middle of this stuff

13:43.432 --> 13:44.392
between me and Jake.

13:44.432 --> 13:45.602
I don't want you
to choose sides.

13:45.652 --> 13:47.002
- Already chose. I'm with you.
- Really?

13:47.042 --> 13:48.092
I didn't know you wanted kids.

13:48.132 --> 13:49.262
I don't know
if I'll ever want kids,

13:49.302 --> 13:50.652
but you should have them.
They're so cute.

13:50.702 --> 13:52.572
It's f****** up.
Aw, it is f****** up.

13:52.612 --> 13:53.742
Anyway, do you want me
to talk to Jake?

13:53.792 --> 13:55.482
- I'm a pretty good bully.
- Thanks, but no.

13:55.532 --> 13:58.102
I've got this covered.
I left him alone with Terry.

13:58.142 --> 13:59.662
That guy is
a walking advertisement

13:59.712 --> 14:00.972
for the joys of fatherhood.

14:01.012 --> 14:04.062
- Do not do it.
- What?

14:04.102 --> 14:05.892
- Don't you love your girls?
- So much.

14:05.932 --> 14:07.152
You should have seen Cagney
this morning

14:07.192 --> 14:09.022
- with her little braids in.
- Oh.

14:09.062 --> 14:10.932
But they are a ton of work, man.

14:10.982 --> 14:13.892
If you are not totally,
100% sure you want them,

14:13.942 --> 14:14.892
you won't survive.

14:14.942 --> 14:16.902
- Is it really that hard?
- Yes.

14:16.942 --> 14:19.252
I never get any sleep.
I'm always sick.

14:19.292 --> 14:21.602
I never get to watch anything
I want on TV.

14:21.642 --> 14:23.252
I still haven't finished
"Breaking Bad,"

14:23.292 --> 14:25.082
but I can recite "Moana"
from memory?

14:25.122 --> 14:28.172
"Maui, shape-shifter,
demigod of the wind and sea.

14:28.212 --> 14:30.782
I am Moana."
Why do I know that?

14:30.822 --> 14:32.002
I don't want to watch
kids' movies.

14:32.042 --> 14:33.522
I want to watch movies
for adults.

14:33.572 --> 14:34.612
Adults and teens.

14:34.652 --> 14:36.262
And they are getting
so manipulative.

14:36.312 --> 14:38.612
Yesterday,
Cagney pretended to be hurt,

14:38.662 --> 14:40.012
I went in to help her,

14:40.052 --> 14:42.272
and Lacey snuck in the kitchen
and stole two cookies.

14:42.312 --> 14:44.102
Oh, my God.
Your children are monsters.

14:44.142 --> 14:45.532
Hey, those are my kids, man.

14:45.582 --> 14:46.712
- Back off.
- Right.

14:46.752 --> 14:49.672
And the crazy part is, I really do
want to go to the water park,

14:49.712 --> 14:51.932
but I can't give that to him
because it's the only card I hold.

14:51.982 --> 14:53.112
Mm.

14:53.152 --> 14:54.592
Elevator.

14:54.632 --> 14:56.852
Excuse me, NYPD.
Can I see your ID?

14:58.502 --> 14:59.772
Amy, behind the wheelchair.

14:59.812 --> 15:01.592
NYPD! Stop!

15:05.862 --> 15:07.952
- Diaz for Jeffords.
- This is Terry.

15:07.992 --> 15:09.212
I think we got our guy.
Colombian man,

15:09.252 --> 15:10.652
unarmed, but he tried to run

15:10.692 --> 15:12.002
as soon as we identified
ourselves.

15:12.042 --> 15:13.652
And he's got a picture of Rojas
on his phone.

15:13.692 --> 15:15.822
We'll be right there.

15:15.872 --> 15:17.652
No one in or out
of this hallway.

15:17.702 --> 15:19.962
Why do you think that guy
is unarmed?

15:20.002 --> 15:21.832
Who knows? Maybe he was
trying to smother Rojas

15:21.872 --> 15:23.142
or unplug his life support.

15:23.182 --> 15:25.922
Or maybe he's a distraction,

15:25.972 --> 15:28.192
and someone else is going
for the cookie jar.

15:28.232 --> 15:29.232
What?

15:33.632 --> 15:36.672
- Hi, Pam.
- Hi, Jake.

15:36.722 --> 15:39.372
Don't come any closer,
or I'll blow us both up!

15:42.811 --> 15:43.621
I'm sorry.

15:43.749 --> 15:45.049
You weren't supposed to be here.

15:45.099 --> 15:46.709
- This wasn't part of the plan.
- It's okay, Pam.

15:46.749 --> 15:48.059
No need to panic.
We're just talking.

15:48.099 --> 15:51.279
Look, I'm just gonna
put this away.

15:51.319 --> 15:53.209
No, Terry,
don't open that, please.

15:53.210 --> 15:54.189
What's going on in there?

15:54.239 --> 15:56.109
There is a woman in here
with an explosive device.

15:56.149 --> 15:58.239
- What? You okay?
- Yep. Everyone is fine.

15:58.279 --> 16:00.239
I just need you to evacuate
this entire floor,

16:00.289 --> 16:02.329
call ESU and the bomb squad
right away,

16:02.369 --> 16:04.379
and jam all cellular
and Wi-Fi signals.

16:04.419 --> 16:05.989
On it.

16:06.029 --> 16:08.819
Okay, Pam, so we're just
gonna stay calm here

16:08.859 --> 16:10.209
and talk this thing through
as friends.

16:10.249 --> 16:12.039
This isn't supposed to be
happening.

16:12.079 --> 16:15.350
The man said that I'd be able
to sneak in here unnoticed.

16:15.351 --> 16:16.581
What man?
Who asked you to do this?

16:16.582 --> 16:18.622
I didn't get his name,
but he was very attractive.

16:18.662 --> 16:20.452
Antonio Banderas could play him
in a movie.

16:20.492 --> 16:21.972
What has he been doing lately?

16:22.022 --> 16:23.892
You know what?
He should be on "Outlander."

16:23.932 --> 16:25.062
Okay, Pam,
I'm gonna cut you off,

16:25.112 --> 16:25.982
but it's not because
I'm not interested.

16:26.022 --> 16:27.112
I'm sorry, I'm nervous.

16:27.152 --> 16:28.202
I get chatty when I get nervous.

16:28.242 --> 16:29.682
This man who gave you the bomb,

16:29.722 --> 16:31.982
did he happen to mention
whether or not it's on a timer

16:32.032 --> 16:33.372
or if there's
a remote detonator?

16:33.422 --> 16:35.682
I don't know.
I'm terrible with electronics.

16:35.722 --> 16:39.162
I wish my son Bobby were here.
He taught me how to iPad.

16:39.212 --> 16:41.172
Okay, I also know how to iPad,

16:41.212 --> 16:42.862
so maybe I could take a look.

16:42.912 --> 16:44.122
Stay where you are!

16:44.172 --> 16:46.002
The man told me
that when I got the bomb set,

16:46.042 --> 16:48.042
I should text him
with this phone

16:48.092 --> 16:49.432
and if anything went wrong,

16:49.482 --> 16:50.782
I should push this button.

16:50.832 --> 16:52.442
No, no, no, no!
You don't want to do that.

16:52.482 --> 16:53.922
Yes, I do.
I have to.

16:53.962 --> 16:55.442
Well, there's only one thing
to do when two people

16:55.482 --> 16:58.012
have diametrically opposing
opinions on a subject.

16:58.052 --> 17:00.012
- Structured debate.
- What?

17:00.052 --> 17:01.192
Yeah, I just learned about it.

17:01.232 --> 17:02.712
All right, I will argue
the negative:

17:02.752 --> 17:03.752
I don't want to blow up.

17:03.802 --> 17:05.192
And you can argue
the affirmative:

17:05.232 --> 17:07.061
you do want to blow up,
which I have to say, Pam,

17:07.102 --> 17:08.452
is a very tough stance to take.

17:08.502 --> 17:09.541
I don't want to blow up,

17:09.582 --> 17:11.852
but the man said
he'd give me $500,000.

17:11.892 --> 17:14.551
This is so Bobby can take care
of my granddaughter.

17:14.592 --> 17:16.462
That girl means the world to me.

17:16.502 --> 17:17.512
Fine, fine.
Point to Pam.

17:17.551 --> 17:19.031
But if you care about her
so much,

17:19.071 --> 17:20.162
how can you just
blow yourself up?

17:20.202 --> 17:21.162
You'll never get to see her again.

17:21.212 --> 17:23.992
Well, at least I know she'll be
financially well taken care of.

17:24.031 --> 17:27.041
Sure, but is this really how
you want her to remember you?

17:27.082 --> 17:28.602
- As a murderer?
- I'd rather be remembered

17:28.652 --> 17:31.132
as a woman who blew up
a mobster to help her family

17:31.172 --> 17:34.782
rather than a librarian whose bowels
are tied up like a sailor's knot!

17:34.832 --> 17:37.702
Okay, that's a very strong argument.
Very strong.

17:37.742 --> 17:38.922
But you're forgetting one thing.

17:38.962 --> 17:40.492
You're not just gonna be
killing a mobster.

17:40.532 --> 17:41.922
You're also gonna be killing me.

17:41.972 --> 17:44.142
He said the blast would only
hurt people in the room.

17:44.182 --> 17:45.582
You could just walk right out of here.

17:45.622 --> 17:48.322
Pam, you know I can't do that.

17:48.362 --> 17:51.412
- Now, please, just give me the bomb.
- And then what?

17:51.452 --> 17:53.282
Bobby doesn't get any money
and I go to jail?

17:53.322 --> 17:54.592
I can't go to jail.

17:54.632 --> 17:56.762
Every roommate I've ever had
has hated me.

17:56.812 --> 17:58.942
In college, I had a roommate
named Mary-Ellen,

17:58.982 --> 18:01.422
and she was dating the brother
of Steve Guttenberg...

18:01.462 --> 18:02.512
Pam, what are we talking
about here?

18:02.552 --> 18:04.072
I'm sorry.
I'm really nervous.

18:04.122 --> 18:05.422
Wait, wait, wait, wait!
I know it probably feels like

18:05.472 --> 18:06.902
you don't have a lot of options
right now.

18:06.952 --> 18:09.472
In fact, this whole situation
probably feels like...

18:09.512 --> 18:11.432
Like a twisted bowel,
but it's not.

18:11.472 --> 18:14.082
There's still one end
of this bowel that's open.

18:14.132 --> 18:16.262
Which end?

18:16.302 --> 18:19.702
- The butt end.
- I'm listening.

18:19.742 --> 18:21.962
Okay, if you hand me
that bomb right now,

18:22.012 --> 18:25.182
nothing bad will have happened,
and that'll be because of you,

18:25.232 --> 18:26.662
because you cooperated.

18:26.712 --> 18:29.402
Also, I'm sure a judge
would understand

18:29.452 --> 18:30.582
how you got into this situation.

18:30.622 --> 18:32.062
I mean, you were asked
to do this

18:32.102 --> 18:34.372
by an Antonio Banderas type.
Who could say no to that?

18:34.412 --> 18:36.412
And even if you do go to prison,

18:36.452 --> 18:38.672
it is gonna be
such a fancy prison.

18:38.722 --> 18:42.372
- With a lot of crafts?
- Yes, with tons of crafts.

18:42.422 --> 18:45.462
Pam, listen to me.

18:45.512 --> 18:48.342
Let's untwist this bowel together.

18:48.382 --> 18:52.172
Let's clear everything out.

18:56.262 --> 18:58.352
Okay.

19:00.172 --> 19:02.572
You did great, Pam.
Thank you.

19:02.612 --> 19:05.222
Now that it's out of my hands,
I can see it really is a bomb.

19:05.272 --> 19:06.352
Yes. Yes, it is.

19:06.402 --> 19:08.972
- Oh, my God, get some help!
- Okay.

19:11.972 --> 19:15.062
- You okay?
- Hey. Yeah, I'm okay.

19:17.152 --> 19:18.322
Really surprised by Pam.

19:18.372 --> 19:20.322
- I did not see that coming.
- Right?

19:20.372 --> 19:22.852
You should have seen the look on
my face when I saw it was her.

19:22.892 --> 19:24.682
Your jaw just dropped.

19:24.722 --> 19:25.942
- Oh, she's right there.
- Mm-hmm.

19:25.982 --> 19:28.552
Good-bye, Pam.
Good luck with everything.

19:28.592 --> 19:30.552
- Kind of liked her in the end.
- Yeah.

19:30.602 --> 19:34.082
- So did they defuse the bomb?
- Yeah, one of 'em.

19:34.122 --> 19:37.042
Oh, you didn't hear?
There was a second bomb.

19:37.082 --> 19:38.342
Ya butt.

19:38.392 --> 19:40.392
- Ya butt is da bomb.
- Aww.

19:40.432 --> 19:42.692
On our anniversary.

19:42.742 --> 19:44.612
Speaking of which,
I requested next week off

19:44.652 --> 19:48.702
so we can take an actual vacation...
to the water park.

19:48.742 --> 19:51.442
I've never been more in love
with you in my entire life.

19:51.492 --> 19:58.282
And hey, I've been thinking,
and I do want to have kids.

19:58.322 --> 20:00.932
With you.

20:00.972 --> 20:04.062
- You're not scared anymore?
- Oh, no, I am so scared.

20:04.112 --> 20:05.332
Maybe even more so than before,

20:05.372 --> 20:07.502
but I was scared in there
with Pam too,

20:07.552 --> 20:10.592
and you know, I didn't panic
or mess anything up there.

20:10.642 --> 20:13.292
If anything, I was sharper.
I was a freakin' debate genius.

20:13.332 --> 20:15.732
Debate genius?
Oh, that's very hot.

20:15.772 --> 20:18.772
Oh, that's an added bonus.
Okay, keep that energy up.

20:18.822 --> 20:22.132
But the point that I was
actually trying to make is,

20:22.172 --> 20:24.742
maybe it's a good thing
that I'm scared of fatherhood.

20:24.782 --> 20:28.172
You know? Maybe it'll turn me
into a freakin' dad genius.

20:31.482 --> 20:33.092
But we don't have to start
trying right away, right?

20:33.142 --> 20:35.962
I mean, I don't know
that I'm all the way there yet.

20:36.012 --> 20:37.922
No, of course not.

20:37.972 --> 20:40.842
Whenever we're both ready.
How do you know when that is?

20:40.882 --> 20:42.542
I guess we'll just
have to have another one

20:42.582 --> 20:45.282
of these really fun,
casual conversations.

20:45.322 --> 20:46.932
Cool. Love that.
Can't wait.

20:48.192 --> 20:50.892
- Can we go home now?
- Yes, please.

20:50.942 --> 20:54.112
Maybe we can grab some Thai food
and brainstorm baby names?

20:54.162 --> 20:55.592
Ooh, I like that.

20:55.642 --> 20:57.992
